RAM BI Dashboard

Business Intelligence platform for analyzing Royal Air Maroc's flight operations — internship project.

The project transforms raw booking/flight data (CSV) into a decision-support dashboard, through an ETL pipeline, a normalized data model (3NF) + star schema, a Laravel API, and a React frontend.

Project structure

RAM-BI-Dashboard/
├── backend/          # Laravel API (routes, controllers, Eloquent models)
├── frontend/          # React application (dashboard, components, charts)
├── database/          # SQL scripts (table creation, ETL, normalization)
└── README.md

Tech stack

LayerTechnologyDatabaseSQL ServerETL / cleaningSQL Server (T-SQL: staging tables, TRY_CONVERT, normalization scripts)BackendLaravel (REST API)FrontendReactMockupFigma

Data model


Vols — fact table (one row = one booking)
LesRoutes — route dimension (City_Pair)
Secteurs — geographic sub-dimension (Sector_Name_Lv2 → Group1)
Agencies — agency dimension (code_agence → Country_Code)


Available KPIs


Total number of passengers
Total number of reservations
Monthly passenger evolution
Monthly reservation evolution
Top 10 routes
Number of passengers per agency


Installation

Backend (Laravel)

bashcd backend
composer install
cp .env.example .env
php artisan key:generate
# configure the SQL Server connection in .env
php artisan serve

Frontend (React)

bashcd frontend
npm install
npm run dev

The API runs by default on http://localhost:8000, the frontend on http://localhost:5173.

Environment variables (backend/.env)

DB_CONNECTION=sqlsrv
DB_HOST=localhost\SQLEXPRESS
DB_PORT=1433
DB_DATABASE=RAM_BI
DB_USERNAME=
DB_PASSWORD=

